        "author_role": "REVIEWER",
        "timestamp": "2018-04-18 20:01:52.000000000",
        "message": "Patch Set 3: Code-Review+1\n\n(1 comment)\n\nTLDR version:  it's a good step forward\n\nLong version:\nI did a fair bit of testing with this, and I'm left wondering if we want to support/allow the NFS provisioner at all.\n\nI did tests where I'd deploy, add new data to the PV, then tear down the deployment and re-deploy.  \n\nWhen the NFS provisioner was enabled, my data did not survive the destroy/re-deploy.  I think this is because the PV was created with a \"Delete\" reclaim policy.  Perhaps this is configurable?  In this case after the destroy, there were no PVC objects left over but there were PVs in the \"Released\" state.  On re-deploy these old PVs were removed and replaced with new ones.\n\nWhen the NFS provisioner is disabled ( our proposed default ), some of the data I created in the PV did survive the destroy/re-deploy.  New files I created by hand stayed around, data in MySQL did not survive though... I think this is a problem for the application to solve, but I'm not sure.  In this case, after the destroy there were no remaining PV or PVC objects but the directory structure where the data resided did remain.",
        "patchset_number": 3
      },
